('w_family_A1_34','live','/lɪv/','verb','살다, 생활하다','To have your home in a particular place.','Three generations {live} in the same house.','3대가 같은 집에서 함께 살아요.','live','A1','family',1,'family house generations home living'),
('w_family_A1_35','home','/hoʊm/','noun','집, 가정','The place where you live or feel you belong.','Coming {home} to family always feels wonderful.','가족이 있는 집으로 돌아오는 건 항상 기분이 좋아요.','home','A1','family',1,'home family warmth cozy living room'),
('w_family_A2_01','relative','/ˈrelətɪv/','noun','친척','A person who is connected to another by birth or marriage.','We invited all our {relatives} to the reunion.','우리는 모든 친척들을 모임에 초대했어요.','relative','A2','family',1,'relatives family gathering reunion celebration'),
('w_family_A2_02','couple','/ˈkʌpl/','noun','커플, 부부','Two people who are in a romantic relationship.','The {couple} celebrated their fifth wedding anniversary.','그 커플은 결혼 5주년을 기념했어요.','couple','A2','family',1,'couple romantic happy anniversary dinner'),
('w_family_A2_03','marriage','/ˈmærɪdʒ/','noun','결혼, 결혼 생활','The legal relationship between a husband and wife.','Their {marriage} has lasted for over thirty years.','그들의 결혼 생활은 30년 이상 지속되고 있어요.','marriage','A2','family',1,'marriage wedding couple rings ceremony'),
